Instruction: With the known‑good 12 V battery installed, use the multimeter to measure DC voltage from the battery positive terminal to the 12 V rail on the PCB (at the junction where the LED/resistor and output cable should connect). Then measure from battery negative to the 0 V rail/output return. Also measure continuity from battery positive to the LED anode pad and to the positive output cable, and from battery negative to the LED cathode pad and to the negative output cable. This checks for any open traces, blown protection devices, or disconnections between the battery and the module’s internal/output rails.
